		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I doubt it, but I'm unsure how SNES ciruit works. You'd have to make sure the cart does not use the positive CE on the 8KB RAM (it should be connected to VCC), and if that's the case you should connect the two highest adress lines of the 32 KB RAM at the correct place (no idea where it's, I'm not really in SNESdev).
<br />
<br />If the positive CE is used then you'd probably need some NAND gates or something like that to combine both CE and /CE to only one /CE.

		

		</td>
